Dialogue: 9,0:03:00.40,0:03:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who said you were going to do it!
Dialogue: 9,0:03:05.87,0:03:08.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please calm down, Mayaka-san...
Dialogue: 9,0:03:08.62,0:03:10.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet, Chii-chan.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:10.54,0:03:13.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you have a reason, but that's besides the point!
Dialogue: 9,0:03:12.50,0:03:14.13,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh right, Mayaka-san!
Dialogue: 9,0:03:13.42,0:03:16.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could have at least called me or something!
Dialogue: 9,0:03:15.13,0:03:16.84,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like some cookies?
Dialogue: 9,0:03:16.21,0:03:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2}This could have been avoided if you had just contacted me!
Dialogue: 9,0:03:19.13,0:03:20.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you had your cell phone with you! {timing check}
Dialogue: 9,0:03:20.09,0:03:22.59,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,I know! How about I go get some milk?
Dialogue: 9,0:03:20.80,0:03:24.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be fine if it were just a hassle for me, but it's not!
Dialogue: 9,0:03:24.01,0:03:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that look?
Dialogue: 9,0:03:25.35,0:03:26.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to me!
Dialogue: 9,0:03:26.76,0:03:28.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand your position here?
Dialogue: 9,0:03:27.72,0:03:31.02,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda Eru doesn't know when to quit.{無謀な人間 (she's reckless to try and get inbetween Ibara and her prey)}
Dialogue: 9,0:03:28.72,0:03:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This won't be fixed just by saying sorry to me.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:31.52,0:03:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I know you're aware of it,
Dialogue: 9,0:03:33.52,0:03:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but you don't have a shred of decency when it matters.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:33.73,0:03:34.98,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't even bother.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:36.61,0:03:39.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't say anything, even though you knew what would happen.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:39.28,0:03:43.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, it rained, it was windy, there was lightning, and even hail fell in the end!
Dialogue: 9,0:03:43.74,0:03:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I spent time picking what to wear, and all of a sudden they're a wreck!
Dialogue: 9,0:03:51.75,0:03:54.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's all your fault!
Dialogue: 9,0:03:53.33,0:03:54.17,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you tired yet?
Dialogue: 9,0:03:55.63,0:03:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:56.59,0:03:58.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then take a break.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:58.09,0:03:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:04.55,0:04:07.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't out to help you!
Dialogue: 9,0:04:07.01,0:04:10.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure can get mad.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:10.39,0:04:12.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bet you let out a lot of stress there.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:12.52,0:04:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you had more common decency, I \Nwouldn't get stressed in the first place.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:16.61,0:04:20.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you should take a lesson from Chitanda-san.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:20.86,0:04:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never even seen her get angry.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:23.70,0:04:32.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you're going to say that, I've never seen you or Oreki-san get angry, either...
Dialogue: 9,0:04:32.08,0:04:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuku-chan totally gets angry.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:33.79,0:04:35.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He really does.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:37.96,0:04:39.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you?
Dialogue: 9,0:04:39.59,0:04:41.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:41.21,0:04:44.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't display it as obviously as Mayaka, but I do every now and then.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:45.18,0:04:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I find that hard to imagine...
Dialogue: 9,0:04:48.80,0:04:52.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I am only human. Of course I get angry.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:52.27,0:04:56.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just don't show your emotions in front of others.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:53.35,0:04:54.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:57.19,0:04:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though it's nothing special when you get angry.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:59.40,0:05:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing special?
Dialogue: 9,0:05:01.36,0:05:03.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really do look down on me...
Dialogue: 9,0:05:03.69,0:05:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm actually a bit curious now...
Dialogue: 9,0:05:07.07,0:05:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can imagine Chitanda planning something to get him riled up.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:13.16,0:05:14.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That could be fun.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:14.91,0:05:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you get angry, Oreki-san?
Dialogue: 9,0:05:18.25,0:05:20.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way he'd get angry.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:20.50,0:05:22.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he's easy going?
Dialogue: 9,0:05:22.21,0:05:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, because he's a sad excuse of a human who can't even get angry.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:27.01,0:05:30.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! That's just mean!
Dialogue: 9,0:05:30.43,0:05:32.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey look, I got angry!
Dialogue: 9,0:05:32.64,0:05:35.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Houtarou's lack of emotions aside,
Dialogue: 9,0:05:35.31,0:05:39.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think Chitanda never getting angry is a special case.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:39.10,0:05:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should try to emulate some of that calmness of hers.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:45.19,0:05:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I can change that part of me just by trying.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:49.11,0:05:50.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't be like Chii-chan.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:50.87,0:05:53.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... that doesn't sound like a compliment...
Dialogue: 9,0:05:53.95,0:05:56.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it might be, actually.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:56.33,0:05:57.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're just making observations.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:57.71,0:05:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're not inherently good or bad.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:59.25,0:06:02.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People who are unable to get angry are a different story,
Dialogue: 9,0:06:02.29,0:06:04.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I think it's an excellent trait not to get angry.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:05.01,0:06:07.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wrath is a serious sin, after all.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:07.34,0:06:10.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you should scale back on your outbursts, Mayaka.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:10.18,0:06:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sin?
Dialogue: 9,0:06:11.14,0:06:13.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The seven deadly sins, right?
Dialogue: 9,0:06:13.43,0:06:15.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep. I figured you'd know, Chitanda-san.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:15.97,0:06:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you've heard of them too, right?
Dialogue: 9,0:06:19.06,0:06:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know of them.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:22.15,0:06:24.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, aren't there 108 sins?
Dialogue: 9,0:06:24.40,0:06:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Buddhism.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:26.44,0:06:27.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:27.57,0:06:28.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 9,0:06:28.32,0:06:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wrath, pride, gluttony, greed...
Dialogue: 9,0:06:33.41,0:06:35.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Envy, lust, and sloth, right?
Dialogue: 9,0:06:35.91,0:06:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, right!
Dialogue: 9,0:06:37.12,0:06:38.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sloth, huh?
Dialogue: 9,0:06:38.66,0:06:40.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you looking at me?
Dialogue: 9,0:06:40.37,0:06:43.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that makes you perfect, Chii-chan.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:43.17,0:06:45.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're diligent, and you don't overeat.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:45.71,0:06:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 9,0:06:47.17,0:06:49.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't imagine you being greedy, and you're definitely not lazy.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:49.97,0:06:50.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 9,0:06:50.76,0:06:53.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you're not into... dirty things.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:53.60,0:06:54.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but...
Dialogue: 9,0:06:54.60,0:06:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to tell if she's envious of anyone, though.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:56.89,0:06:59.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those two aren't even complimenting her anymore...
Dialogue: 9,0:06:59.81,0:07:01.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're just teasing her.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:01.52,0:07:02.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's stop this!
Dialogue: 9,0:07:02.94,0:07:06.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, when I get hungry I can eat a lot!
Dialogue: 9,0:07:02.94,0:07:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}She doesn't seem the envious type, either.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:06.36,0:07:07.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So would anyone.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:07.53,0:07:09.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should just call her Saint Eru.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:10.24,0:07:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't "Chitanda Eru" sound kind of angelic?
Dialogue: 9,0:07:13.49,0:07:16.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uriel, Gabriel, Chitandael?
Dialogue: 9,0:07:19.04,0:07:20.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please stop it!
Dialogue: 9,0:07:22.04,0:07:23.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She got angry.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:23.25,0:07:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She told us off, too.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:25.79,0:07:27.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Chii-chan.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:27.88,0:07:29.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever!
Dialogue: 9,0:07:29.84,0:07:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, now you made her mad.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:33.51,0:07:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were totally playing along, too.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:38.31,0:07:41.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think it's good thing to never get angry.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:41.98,0:07:44.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same for the other deadly sins, right?
Dialogue: 9,0:07:46.69,0:07:49.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think pride and greed are also important.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:50.15,0:07:50.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How?
Dialogue: 9,0:07:51.57,0:07:57.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you can never feel pride, then that means you have no self confidence.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:57.53,0:08:03.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And someone who never feels greed wouldn't be able to support their family.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:03.87,0:08:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,New technologies would never have been invented if people never felt envy.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:12.55,0:08:16.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... I didn't mean to turn this into a lecture...
Dialogue: 9,0:08:17.97,0:08:19.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Interesting...
Dialogue: 9,0:08:19.72,0:08:22.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're saying that it's a matter of degree?
Dialogue: 9,0:08:22.68,0:08:30.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think it's useful to just take the deadly sins as absolute and apply that to our lives.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:30.69,0:08:34.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you don't think it's necessarily bad to get angry?
Dialogue: 9,0:08:34.57,0:08:35.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:35.95,0:08:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you can never get angry at anything, that probably means you have nothing that you like, either.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:41.08,0:08:43.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do get angry. Yep.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:43.71,0:08:47.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if that's the case, why don't you ever get angry?
Dialogue: 9,0:08:47.58,0:08:48.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because it tires me out.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:48.92,0:08:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I like to avoid getting tired.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:01.43,0:09:04.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda-san's been poisoned by Houtarou!
Dialogue: 9,0:09:04.77,0:09:06.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad!
Dialogue: 9,0:09:06.06,0:09:08.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a ghost haunting Kamiyama High!
Dialogue: 9,0:09:08.56,0:09:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ghost of energy saving!
Dialogue: 9,0:09:10.52,0:09:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wake up, Chii-chan!
Dialogue: 9,0:09:12.32,0:09:13.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Chii-chan!
Dialogue: 9,0:09:12.32,0:09:14.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These guys sure run their mouths...
Dialogue: 9,0:09:14.90,0:09:16.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just joking!
Dialogue: 9,0:09:17.78,0:09:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a joke.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:21.74,0:09:22.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A joke, huh?
Dialogue: 9,0:09:22.99,0:09:25.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And here I thought I'd found a soul mate.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:26.16,0:09:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I was just playing around.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:31.17,0:09:34.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I can get angry. And I do.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:36.13,0:09:39.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like, for example...
Dialogue: 9,0:09:42.22,0:09:45.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get angry when people waste food.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:45.10,0:09:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each grain of rice is a drop of sweat.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:48.98,0:09:52.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a farmer's daughter for you.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:52.15,0:09:53.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That reminds me...
Dialogue: 9,0:09:53.90,0:09:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On that topic, wasn't it you who got angry in Omichi's class during fifth period?
Dialogue: 9,0:10:02.83,0:10:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 9,0:10:04.66,0:10:06.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could I forget?
Dialogue: 9,0:10:07.79,0:10:11.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was hoping I could ask you about that!
Dialogue: 9,0:10:11.84,0:10:12.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crap.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:13.30,0:10:14.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm curious!
Dialogue: 9,0:10:14.09,0:10:15.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm curious! I'm curious!
Dialogue: 9,0:10:15.88,0:10:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm curious! I'm curious! I'm curious!
Dialogue: 9,0:10:25.18,0:10:27.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll go home now.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:28.94,0:10:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was hoping I could ask you about that!
Dialogue: 9,0:10:36.74,0:10:38.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 9,0:10:38.32,0:10:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. During fifth period in math class, I got angry.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:46.29,0:10:47.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got angry?
Dialogue: 9,0:10:47.87,0:10:53.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't know what happened to make me angry.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:53.59,0:10:56.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was no need for me to suddenly get angry,
Dialogue: 9,0:10:56.96,0:11:00.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but something happened to make me angry,
Dialogue: 9,0:11:00.38,0:11:03.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I don't know what it was that happened.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:06.18,0:11:06.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say what?
Dialogue: 9,0:11:06.93,0:11:10.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said, I'm not sure what...
Dialogue: 9,0:11:13.48,0:11:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Either ways, I'm curious!
