Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.69,0:11:20.03,Episode Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an5\pos(636,349.733)\fad(250,0)\b1\c&H030004&\fscx151\fscy156}Hyouka
Dialogue: 9,0:11:23.11,0:11:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fifth period today was math class.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:25.95,0:11:28.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi-sensei is our teacher for that.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:28.08,0:11:33.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you already know what kind of teacher he is.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:33.92,0:11:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, let me explain from the beginning.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:36.59,0:11:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 9,0:11:38.67,0:11:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He arrived pretty much just as the bell chimed.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:42.97,0:11:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right before he entered the classroom, he stopped for a moment and looked at the class name plate.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:49.77,0:11:52.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything up until that point was fairly normal.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:53.35,0:11:57.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He started off by writing down a quadratic equation on the blackboard.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:57.94,0:12:05.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The equation was simple, but he included a restriction on the domain of x.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.07,0:12:05.91,Handwriting,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fs80\b1\frz11.6\c&HBBC9C1&\pos(1160,545)}Domain{\b0}
Dialogue: 9,0:12:05.87,0:12:12.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then he singled out Kawasaki-san and told him to draw the range of Y.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:13.12,0:12:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kawasaki-san looked obviously confused.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:16.00,0:12:17.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, that's right.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:17.29,0:12:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We hadn't learned anything about domain restrictions yet.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:22.17,0:12:25.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kawasaki-san said he didn't know how to.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:25.30,0:12:30.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then Omichi-sensei got mad and began to berate us.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:30.93,0:12:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He told Tamura-san, who's quite skilled at math, to answer next.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:34.73,0:12:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he couldn't answer it either.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:38.02,0:12:44.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this point I realized that he had mistaken how far we'd gotten in the textbook.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:44.61,0:12:48.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Others in the class began to realize too, and it started to get rowdy.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:48.58,0:12:53.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the teacher got even angrier and yelled at us.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:54.16,0:12:55.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:55.37,0:12:58.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was striking the blackboard as he reprimanded us.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:59.38,0:13:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think there were people in the class who could have solved it, but we had all gone silent.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:06.22,0:13:11.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi-sensei once again singled out Tamura-san and yelled at him.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:12.14,0:13:14.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's when I stood up.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:14.60,0:13:20.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked him to double-check where we were supposed to be in the textbook.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:20.15,0:13:23.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah yes, that's when I got angry.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:24.86,0:13:26.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened after that?
Dialogue: 9,0:13:26.95,0:13:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After he took a look, he muttered "Oh, right," and then apologized.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:33.91,0:13:37.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He told Tamura-san to sit down again, and then class resumed as normal.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:38.33,0:13:40.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how Omichi is?
Dialogue: 9,0:13:40.96,0:13:47.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously. I went through a lot of trouble after the midterms because of him.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:47.05,0:13:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We had teachers like him in elementary and middle school too.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:50.72,0:13:52.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like he's a bad teacher or anything.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:52.97,0:13:56.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you can't blame him for failing your tests.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:56.10,0:13:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd better make it up at the end of term.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:57.85,0:13:58.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 9,0:13:59.27,0:14:01.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So anyway, what do you think?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:04.78,0:14:07.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there something strange about that story?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:12.74,0:14:14.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What I wanted to ask you was,
Dialogue: 9,0:14:14.91,0:14:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why did he make that mistake in the first place?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:18.83,0:14:22.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not the type to do that...
Dialogue: 9,0:14:22.59,0:14:23.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:23.88,0:14:28.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi is pretty strict, but that's because he's strict on himself too.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:28.76,0:14:31.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then why did he make that mistake?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:31.51,0:14:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I don't get.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:32.76,0:14:34.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get it either.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:35.18,0:14:36.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-san!
Dialogue: 9,0:14:36.02,0:14:36.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No idea.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:36.98,0:14:42.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go look inside his head and find out yourself.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:42.15,0:14:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This would be simple if I could do that.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:44.15,0:14:46.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Well that's too bad.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:46.44,0:14:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just give up then.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:47.78,0:14:49.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm curious!
Dialogue: 9,0:14:49.65,0:14:51.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please help me figure this out!
Dialogue: 9,0:14:51.66,0:14:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why me?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:53.32,0:14:57.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can figure it out if you just think about it a little!
Dialogue: 9,0:14:57.62,0:15:00.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give me the "You can do it if you try!" speech.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:00.62,0:15:04.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chii-chan, you shouldn't expect too much from him.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:04.59,0:15:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a grasshopper in his previous life.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:06.92,0:15:09.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka-san, you can see people's former incarnations?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:09.55,0:15:11.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice diversion, Ibara!
Dialogue: 9,0:15:12.09,0:15:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But right now I'm curious about our teacher.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:14.51,0:15:16.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, she's persistent.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:16.68,0:15:19.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm curious! {かっ。。かわええ。。。}
Dialogue: 9,0:15:26.73,0:15:30.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After class, Omichi-sensei always writes a note in his textbook.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:30.65,0:15:32.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know why?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:32.78,0:15:36.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To keep track of how far in the curriculum he went that class?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:36.49,0:15:37.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I think too.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:37.91,0:15:42.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And before entering a class he always checks the name plate.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:42.62,0:15:47.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like he's got all his bases covered, so where did his mistake come from?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:47.25,0:15:54.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm guessing his memos are like "July 1st, class A" on page 15 or something.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:54.64,0:15:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has to contain at least that much in order to know how far he's gone.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:58.77,0:16:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he got the date wrong?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:01.18,0:16:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That might have made him backtrack, but it couldn't have caused him to skip ahead.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:04.73,0:16:06.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Use your brain.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:07.23,0:16:08.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that's true...
Dialogue: 9,0:16:09.82,0:16:12.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mind if I ask something?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:12.11,0:16:13.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:13.36,0:16:16.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can understand why you'd get angry.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:16.49,0:16:21.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I wouldn't want to talk back to a teacher like that.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:21.12,0:16:22.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So why did you?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:22.91,0:16:29.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was angry, but not because he was yelling at us.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:29.09,0:16:32.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then was it because there were people who could have answered but didn't?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:32.13,0:16:32.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:33.55,0:16:37.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think anyone wanted to stick their neck out in that situation.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:37.72,0:16:41.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, because other people realized his mistake but didn't say anything?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:41.93,0:16:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 9,0:16:45.48,0:16:47.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you felt sorry for Tamura, then?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:50.11,0:16:55.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I certainly felt sorry for him, but I don't think I'd get angry over that.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:55.78,0:17:02.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2}After all, I can understand why he'd yell at students who \Ndidn't seem to remember anything from the previous class.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:03.45,0:17:06.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what was it that made me angry?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:09.84,0:17:12.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I find myself hard to understand sometimes.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:13.63,0:17:14.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:14.97,0:17:23.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still don't know enough about Chitanda to know what makes her angry or happy.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:23.47,0:17:25.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Oreki-san?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:28.40,0:17:34.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's safe to assume that Omichi was writing down the class' progress in his textbook.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:34.32,0:17:36.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet he was mistaken.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:36.90,0:17:44.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2}The fact that he carried on anyway means that the previous \Npage must have had a note saying he'd already done it.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:44.29,0:17:49.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your class hadn't been taught domains yet, right?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:49.54,0:17:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:51.34,0:17:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what if you had?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:55.63,0:17:57.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:57.55,0:18:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi teaches math every year.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:00.68,0:18:03.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At some point, last year's 1-A learned it.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:04.39,0:18:08.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're saying he might have mistaken last year's notes, I'm afraid that's impossible.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:08.64,0:18:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 9,0:18:10.35,0:18:14.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The teachers get new textbooks every year.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:14.40,0:18:19.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They need to have the latest revisions to stay consistent with the students, right?
Dialogue: 9,0:18:19.57,0:18:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi is using this year's 4th edition.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:23.70,0:18:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 9,0:18:25.58,0:18:28.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're filled with useless knowledge, as usual.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:28.58,0:18:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a database, after all.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:33.46,0:18:38.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's the possibility that he mixed up the notes he wrote.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:38.51,0:18:42.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm sure Chitanda wouldn't accept that answer.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:46.39,0:18:48.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really don't get domains, though.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:49.06,0:18:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's already hard enough for me to just draw the x and y axes.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:54.27,0:18:58.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be scary to be singled out by Omichi.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:58.03,0:18:58.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:59.61,0:19:02.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1-D has already learned domains?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:02.91,0:19:04.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we have.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:04.41,0:19:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi's class already did domains, but my class and Chitanda's class haven't yet...
Dialogue: 9,0:19:12.63,0:19:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:15.42,0:19:18.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That face tells me you've thought of something.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:18.76,0:19:19.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:20.30,0:19:21.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:21.26,0:19:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 9,0:19:21.80,0:19:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure that he made a note a page ahead of where you'd gotten to?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:27.60,0:19:28.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I believe so.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:28.98,0:19:35.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Additionally, the note was written this year, and shows the class' progress.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:35.06,0:19:36.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:37.11,0:19:41.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if the memo he wrote wasn't, in fact, for your class?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:41.61,0:19:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if it was actually Satoshi's class' memo?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:45.12,0:19:46.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My class?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:50.33,0:19:54.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi is in charge of classes A, B, C, and D, right?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:54.92,0:19:59.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it wasn't A or B, that doesn't mean it has to be class D's.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:59.59,0:20:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And anyway, why class D?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:04.18,0:20:08.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because it's quite possible he mixed the two up.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:09.60,0:20:12.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C is clearly nothing like A.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:12.44,0:20:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Are you an idiot?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:15.40,0:20:17.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A and D aren't anything alike either.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:17.90,0:20:20.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi teaches math.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:20.07,0:20:20.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:21.86,0:20:26.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A math teacher has a much higher chance of mixing up A and D.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:26.53,0:20:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.49,0:20:51.14,Handwriting,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fs35\b0\c&H2B2B2B&\pos(1005.33,650.667)}Oreki Houtarou's writing{\b1}
Dialogue: 9,0:20:29.99,0:20:38.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's say he wrote "July 1st, A" on page 10, and "July 1st, D" on page 15.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:38.17,0:20:39.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, so what?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:40.42,0:20:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could he have mixed those up?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:42.59,0:20:47.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he had mistaken the D for an A, that would explain what happened.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:48.68,0:20:51.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,True, but how?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:51.35,0:20:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A math teacher would have written them like this.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:57.86,0:21:00.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Lower case A and D!
Dialogue: 9,0:21:01.07,0:21:01.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it now!
Dialogue: 9,0:21:03.69,0:21:05.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That makes sense...
Dialogue: 9,0:21:05.24,0:21:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I lost points on an English test because the teacher couldn't tell the difference in my handwriting.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:11.04,0:21:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you too?
Dialogue: 9,0:21:13.16,0:21:16.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In my case, it was "n" and "h".
Dialogue: 9,0:21:16.37,0:21:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that does seem likely.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:19.79,0:21:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally cleared that up.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:24.63,0:21:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A and D...
Dialogue: 9,0:21:26.34,0:21:28.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can understand the mistake now.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:28.55,0:21:33.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I may have gone too far in what I said to him.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:33.31,0:21:35.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was wrong of me.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:38.31,0:21:39.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you say that?
Dialogue: 9,0:21:39.81,0:21:41.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi was in the wrong!
Dialogue: 9,0:21:41.40,0:21:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He deserved anything you said to him!
Dialogue: 9,0:21:43.32,0:21:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And besides—
Dialogue: 9,0:21:44.53,0:21:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:45.90,0:21:49.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's getting pretty late. We should head home.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:49.03,0:21:51.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Fuku-chan!
Dialogue: 9,0:21:51.28,0:21:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine, Mayaka.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:52.70,0:21:54.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mystery's solved.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:54.54,0:21:58.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I mean! Fuku-chan!
Dialogue: 9,0:21:59.25,0:22:01.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The normally calm Chitanda got angry.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:01.50,0:22:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so she wanted to know why.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:04.05,0:22:12.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She said it's not necessarily bad to get angry, but the truth is, she never wants to.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:12.89,0:22:15.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Houtarou, Chitanda-san. We should go.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:12.89,0:22:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2}Perhaps Chitanda wanted Omichi to have had his reasons, and \Nwanted to believe that she got angry because of her own mistake.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:15.98,0:22:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Ah, right. Let me clean up.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:24.07,0:22:27.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe Chitanda Eru is just that kind of person?
Dialogue: 9,0:22:28.28,0:22:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. What do I know about her?
Dialogue: 9,0:22:35.33,0:22:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I can predict her actions sometimes, I couldn't hope to understand her heart.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:42.34,0:22:46.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That'd be a deadly sin, just like she was saying.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:46.88,0:22:48.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Pride".
Dialogue: 9,0:22:49.13,0:22:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd better watch out.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:52.14,0:22:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even just today, how many times already has Chitanda done or said something unexpected?
Dialogue: 9,0:22:57.48,0:22:58.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-san?
Dialogue: 9,0:22:58.93,0:23:00.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you going home?
Dialogue: 9,0:23:00.85,0:23:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yeah...
Dialogue: 9,0:23:04.73,0:23:06.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-san.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:06.73,0:23:08.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:09.36,0:23:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems all you do is help me out.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:14.33,0:23:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, and it's a hassle.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:20.54,0:23:22.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 9,0:23:22.63,0:23:24.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you coming?
Dialogue: 9,0:23:24.71,0:23:27.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we're coming now.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:27.38,0:23:28.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:35.64,0:23:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I'll finish tomorrow.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:39.06,0:23:40.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.81,0:23:44.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}That might be true for you, Mayaka, but just think about it...
Dialogue: 9,0:23:47.86,0:23:52.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so today, more of my high school life was squandered away.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:52.95,0:23:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Personally, I think sloth is more than enough sin for me.
